{
  "texts": [
    "The scaled density κ(θ) is known as the convergence.",
    "We will see the reason for this name in Sect. 3.4.",
    "There is no single standard name for τ (θ, β), but Fermat potential, (scaled) time delay, or arrival time are all used.",
    "The quantities κ, ψ, and α behave analogously to the density, classical gravitational potential, and force.",
    "In particular, a circular mass distribution behaves like a point mass when observed from outside."
  ]
}